---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'AI Website Building Guide: How to Build Fast (2025)',
  description: 'Complete guide to building websites with AI. Durable, v0.dev, Framer compared. Which tool to use for your needs. Speed vs ownership tradeoff explained.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['AI website builder', 'how to build a website with AI', 'Durable vs v0', 'AI web design', 'no-code website builder'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Complete Guide · Updated 2025
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        AI Website Building: Complete Guide
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Building websites with AI used to be science fiction. Now it's done in 30 seconds. But speed isn't everything. Here's how to choose the right AI builder for your actual needs.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Use <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink> to prototype fast. Rebuild with <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> if you want code ownership. Use <AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink> for visual control without coding.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Different tools for different needs. Speed vs ownership vs control. Pick based on what actually matters for your project, not marketing hype.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The 3 Main Approaches -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Three Ways to Build with AI
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Durable -->
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-2xl mb-4">1. <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink>: Generate Everything</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Answer a few questions about your business. AI generates complete website with multiple sections, copy, images, contact forms. 30 seconds from prompt to published site.</p>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Best for:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>• Non-technical users</li>
          <li>• MVP testing (validate ideas fast)</li>
          <li>• Local businesses (plumbers, salons, restaurants)</li>
          <li>• People who need a site NOW</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Tradeoff:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">No code ownership. You can't export. Permanently locked into Durable platform. $15-30/month forever or lose your site.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- v0.dev -->
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-2xl mb-4">2. <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink>: Generate Code</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Describe what you want. AI writes React/Next.js code. You iterate with prompts. Download the actual code. Host yourself or on <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> for free.</p>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Best for:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>• Developers who know React/Next.js</li>
          <li>• People who want code ownership</li>
          <li>• Projects requiring customization</li>
          <li>• Long-term assets (build once, own forever)</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Tradeoff:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Requires technical skill. If you can't code, this isn't for you. Slower than Durable but gives you full control and ownership.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Framer -->
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-2xl mb-4">3. <AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink>: Visual Builder with AI</h3>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Drag-and-drop website builder with AI features. Design manually when you want. Use AI to generate sections or pages. Export possible (but messy).</p>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Best for:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <li>• Designers who think visually</li>
          <li>• Marketing sites and landing pages</li>
          <li>• People who want more control than Durable</li>
          <li>• Freelancers building client sites</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Tradeoff:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Monthly subscription ($5-30/mo). Export is possible but not production-ready. You're mostly locked in, but with better visual tools than Durable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Which Should You Choose? -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Decision Tree: Which Tool for You?
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Question 1 -->
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-4">Question 1: Can you code (or want to learn)?</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-bold mb-2">✓ Yes, I know React/Next.js (or want to learn)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">→ Use <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink>. You'll get full code ownership and unlimited customization. Free tier is generous. Deploy to <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> for free hosting. Best long-term investment.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-purple-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-bold mb-2">✗ No, I'm non-technical</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">→ Go to Question 2</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Question 2 -->
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-4">Question 2: Do you care about owning your website code?</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-purple-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-bold mb-2">✓ Yes, I want to be able to leave the platform</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">→ You have two options: Learn to code and use <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink>, or hire a developer to rebuild in <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> after validating with <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink>. Ownership requires technical skill or money.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-purple-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-bold mb-2">✗ No, I just need the site to work</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">→ Go to Question 3</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Question 3 -->
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-4">Question 3: What's more important - speed or design control?</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-purple-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-bold mb-2">Speed: I need a site TODAY</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">→ Use <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink>. 30 seconds to complete site. Zero technical skill required. You're locked in, but you'll have a working site fast enough to validate your business idea.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-bold mb-2">Control: I care about design and customization</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">→ Use <AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink>. Visual builder with AI features. More design control than Durable. Still requires monthly payment but gives you better tools to create something unique.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Smart Workflow -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      The Smart Workflow: Prototype, Then Rebuild
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
      <p class="font-black mb-4">Best practice: Don't marry the first AI builder you try. Use them for what they're good at.</p>

      <ol class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Phase 1: Rapid Prototyping (Day 1)</strong>
          <p class="ml-6">Use <AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink> to generate a site in 30 seconds. Get instant structure and copy. See what your business looks like online.</p>
        </li>

        <li><strong>Phase 2: Validation (Week 1-2)</strong>
          <p class="ml-6">Customize the content. Make it sound like you, not AI. Test the layout. Show it to potential customers. Get feedback. Validate the business idea.</p>
        </li>

        <li><strong>Phase 3: Rebuild Decision (Month 1)</strong>
          <p class="ml-6">If business validates, decide: Is Durable's $180-360/year worth it? Or should you rebuild properly?</p>
          <ul class="ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>• <strong>Technical?</strong> Rebuild with <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> + Next.js for full ownership</li>
            <li>• <strong>Design-focused?</strong> Rebuild with Framer for visual control</li>
            <li>• <strong>Neither?</strong> Keep using Durable or hire someone</li>
          </ul>
        </li>

        <li><strong>Phase 4: Migration</strong>
          <p class="ml-6">Copy your custom content (the only thing that actually mattered from Durable). Paste into your new site. Launch properly owned asset.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mt-6">You get AI speed for ideation. You get ownership for long-term. Best of both worlds.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cost Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Real Cost Over 5 Years
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-l-4 border-purple-600 p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2"><AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink>: $900-1,800 over 5 years</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">$15-30/month × 60 months. Stop paying, lose the site. Year 1: $180-360. Year 5: $900-1,800 total.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2"><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink>: $0-1,200 over 5 years</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Free for code generation. <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> Pro is $20/mo for custom domain (optional). Year 1: $0-240. Year 5: $0-1,200 total. You own the code forever.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2"><AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink>: $300-1,800 over 5 years</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">$5-30/month × 60 months. Export possible but not clean. Year 1: $60-360. Year 5: $300-1,800 total. Similar to Durable but with better design tools.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2">The math:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">v0.dev is cheapest long-term if you're technical. Durable and Framer cost more over time but include hosting and support. Choose based on your time horizon and skills, not just short-term price.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What AI Can't Do -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What AI Can't Do (Yet)
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">AI generates generic websites</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Durable, v0.dev, Framer all produce cookie-cutter results initially. Customization makes them yours. If you ship what AI generates, your site looks like every other AI site.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">AI copy needs human rewriting</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">AI-generated text is usable but boring. Generic. Lacks your voice. Rewrite everything. Add your personality, stories, specific details. Make it sound like a human wrote it.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">AI can't fix strategic problems</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">AI builds what you ask for. If your idea is bad, AI builds a bad idea beautifully. Validation happens before the site, not through the site. AI won't save a business nobody wants.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">AI can't replace design skills</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">AI generates competent designs, not remarkable ones. Understanding spacing, typography, color theory — these skills make the difference between looks fine and looks amazing. AI gets you to 80%. You take it to 100%.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Success Stories -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Real Workflow Examples
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">Example 1: Local Plumber (Non-technical)</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Used Durable. Generated site in 30 seconds. Added local service area, phone number, photos of actual work. $15/month. Gets 3-5 calls per week. Perfect fit. Doesn't care about code ownership.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">Example 2: SaaS Founder (Technical)</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Used Durable to prototype landing page. Validated product idea with 50 beta signups. Then rebuilt landing page with v0.dev + Next.js. Now owns code, hosts on <AffiliateLink href="https://vercel.com">Vercel</AffiliateLink> free. Paid $15 for one month of Durable. Saved hundreds long-term.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">Example 3: Marketing Freelancer (Designer)</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Uses Framer for all client landing pages. Visual control means faster iterations. $30/month Pro plan pays for itself with one client project. Exports code to give clients if they insist (though messy). Clients happy with results.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">Example 4: What NOT to Do</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Non-technical user chose v0.dev because "free." Generated React code but couldn't customize it. Couldn't deploy it. Stuck with code they can't use. Should have chosen Durable or Framer. Right tool, wrong job.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">AI website builders are tools. Not magic. Different tools for different jobs:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• <strong><AffiliateLink href="https://durable.co">Durable</AffiliateLink></strong> — Non-technical users who value speed over ownership</li>
        <li>• <strong><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink></strong> — Developers who want code and full control</li>
        <li>• <strong><AffiliateLink href="https://framer.com">Framer</AffiliateLink></strong> — Designers who want visual control with AI help</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Best approach:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• Use Durable for rapid prototyping and idea validation</li>
        <li>• If business validates, rebuild with v0 (if technical) or Framer (if design-focused)</li>
        <li>• Get AI speed now without sacrificing long-term ownership</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">Don't choose based on marketing hype. Choose based on: your technical skill, ownership needs, and time horizon. Prototype with AI, rebuild properly if the idea works.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related AI Builder Guides
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/durable-ai-review" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable AI Full Review</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">30-second website generation</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/durable-vs-v0-vs-framer" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable vs v0 vs Framer</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Detailed comparison</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
